                                                                                                 NIST SP 800-160, VOL. 2, REV. 1                                         DEVELOPING CYBER-RESILIENT SYSTEMS
                                                                                                 _________________________________________________________________________________________________



                                                                                                  resilient otherwise             Security considerations applied to enable system operation
                                                                                                  [SP 800-160 v1]                 despite disruption while not maintaining a secure mode, state,
                                                                                                                                  or transition; or only being able to provide for partial security
                                                                                                                                  within a given system mode, state, or transition.
                                                                                                                                  See securely resilient.
                                                                                                  risk                            A measure of the extent to which an entity is threatened by a
                                                                                                  [CNSSI 4009]                    potential circumstance or event, and typically a function of the
                                                                                                  [OMB A-130]                     adverse impacts that would arise if the circumstance or event
                                                                                                                                  occurs; and the likelihood of occurrence.
This publication is available free of charge from: https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-160v2r1




                                                                                                  risk analysis                   Process to comprehend the nature of risk and to determine the
                                                                                                  [ISO 73]                        level of risk.
                                                                                                  risk assessment                 The process of identifying risks to organizational operations
                                                                                                  [ISO 73]                        (including mission, functions, image, reputation), organizational
                                                                                                  [SP 800-39, adapted]            assets, individuals, other organizations, and the Nation, resulting
                                                                                                                                  from the operation of an information system. A part of risk
                                                                                                                                  management incorporates threat and vulnerability analyses, and
                                                                                                                                  considers mitigations provided by security controls planned or in
                                                                                                                                  place.
                                                                                                                                  Overall process of risk identification, risk analysis, and risk
                                                                                                                                  evaluation.
                                                                                                  risk-adaptive access            Access privileges are granted based on a combination of a user’s
                                                                                                  control                         identity, mission need, and the level of security risk that exists
                                                                                                  [SP 800-95]                     between the system being accessed and a user. RAdAC will use
                                                                                                                                  security metrics, such as the strength of the authentication
                                                                                                                                  method, the level of assurance of the session connection
                                                                                                                                  between the system and a user, and the physical location of a
                                                                                                                                  user, to make its risk determination.
                                                                                                  risk factor                     A characteristic used in a risk model as an input for determining
                                                                                                  [SP 800-30]                     the level of risk in a risk assessment.
                                                                                                  risk framing                    Risk framing is the set of assumptions, constraints, risk
                                                                                                  [SP 800-39]                     tolerances, and priorities/trade-offs that shape an organization’s
                                                                                                                                  approach for managing risk.
                                                                                                  risk management                 Strategy that addresses how organizations intend to assess risk,
                                                                                                  strategy                        respond to risk, and monitor risk—making explicit and
                                                                                                  [SP 800-39]                     transparent the risk perceptions that organizations routinely use
                                                                                                                                  in making both investment and operational decisions.
                                                                                                  risk model                      A key component of a risk assessment methodology (in addition
                                                                                                  [SP 800-30]                     to assessment approach and analysis approach) that defines key
                                                                                                                                  terms and assessable risk factors.
                                                                                                  risk response                   Accepting, avoiding, mitigating, sharing, or transferring risk to
                                                                                                  [SP 800-39]                     organizational operations (i.e., mission, functions, image, or
                                                                                                                                  reputation), organizational assets, individuals, other
                                                                                                                                  organizations, or the Nation.



